  "texts": [
    "Others use a Control Flow Graph (CFG) for path-based calculations [7], or model the search for the longest path as an Integer Linear Programming problem [8,9].Accurately estimating WCET is a complex yet crucial endeavor for ensuring the reliability and efficiency of real-time systems.",
    "The challenge is compounded by the increasing complexity of software algorithms and hardware architectures, which introduce a multitude of execution paths and potential bottlenecks.",
    "Traditional WCET analysis methods, primarily static in nature, often fall short in fully capturing the nuanced behaviors of these advanced systems.",
    "These methods struggle to account for the dynamic interplay between software and hardware, potentially leading to inaccurate estimations of execution times.",
    "Static analysis can sometimes produce overly pessimistic estimations that may not reflect real-world execution times [10]."
  ],
